<h3>Java Programming</h3>

<p>Penn State's Computer Science 221, is an intensive Java course focusing on topics such as the following:</p>

<ul class="course_topics">
	<li>Polymorphism</li>
	<li>Multi-Threading</li>
	<li>Multiple Inheritance</li>
	<li>Factory methods</li>
	<li>Graphical Programming</li>
	<li>Database interaction</li>
	<li>Java Server Pages</li>
	<li>Semaphore locking / Dead-Locks / Live-Locks (& Dining Philosopher Problem)</li>
	<li>Advanced Tcp/IP socket programming</li>
</ul>

<p>Another major goal of this course aimed to help us realize the need for better object-oriented design practices and efficient algorithms while maintaining clean, scalable code.</p>

<h3>Core Projects in this course included:</h3>
	<ul class="course_topics">
	<li>Interactive Chat Rooms & Servers over both TCP / UDP Sockets</li>
	<li>Movie Database Retrieval / Management System</li>
	<li>Graphical Scrabble Gamerooms and Game Servers Implementation</li>
	<li>JSP Website Showcase & Java Applet Conversions</li>
</ul>

